This paper deals with the deployment of wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also formulates the problem as a Markov decision process and proposes learning algorithms, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also considers the trade-off between power usage and outage probabilities, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes heuristic algorithms and learning algorithms, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG).
